<P>It's always&nbsp;exciting to think of new classes, but I personally feel that it would be better to focus on getting the balance right among the existing classes before introducing new ones. The berserker class is at least an example of what NOT to do (rush a new class with a lot of issues - no offense to any berserkers out there <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>).</P>
